HEADWORD: Carse
<hw>Carse</hw> <pr>(k⟦aum⟧rs)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of Celtic
origin; cf. W. <ets>cars</ets> bog, fen. <ets>carsen</ets> reed, Armor.
<ets>kars</ets>, <ets>korsen</ets>, bog plant, reed.]</ety> <def>Low,
fertile land; a river valley.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jomieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

